Been contemplating for over a year now. Been getting a bit worse, but I suppose I've had my moments. I would have missed my little miracle kitten that has saved me from many panic attacks, he just knows when I'm upset. Nothing like a purring kitten forcing itself into you lap and shoving their face into your mouth. That's how he hugs. Would have missed the My Chemical Romance reunion tour announcement. They saved my life all those years ago, and it's cool to see them make a return. Wouldn't have ended up reading the Harry Potter books before I died. Wouldn't have seen all the movies either. Wouldn't have picked up the guitar again after a few years of not playing. I wouldn't have written any songs myself. I never would have met a good friend that I have through the internet. Hell, thinking about it, there's a lot of small things that have made my past year pretty okay, despite being depressed and homeless. Makes me rethink a bit, I s'pose.

Actully, I had this done once! I had dropped like a 35-40 pound container of litter on my toe. I thought it was just bruised because of the odd coloring, but after I literally couldn't walk because of the pain I went into the ER to see what the fuck was happening. (It was like 3hrs before I went in, but it kept getting worse over time). They had my foot X-rayed to make sure I didn't break anything, and they told me there was a shit ton of blood trapped under my toenail. They drilled a hole right through the center and wrapped it, so that it wasn't exposed. I felt immediate pressure relief. The only pain I felt was from it already hurting. It felt fucking great. I still couldn't walk without being in serious pain, but it still felt better. It took like 4 days to drain out completely. My nail eventually grew out and there's no sign that it ever happened.
